games.comment: James Starks, a talented back out of Buffalo who hasn't been able to play because of injuries, rushed for 73 yards on 18 carries. Those may not be overly impressive numbers at first glance, but they are when you consider that the 49ers ranked third against the run going into this weekend. Pick up Starks immediately.    With Starks running well, everything was clicking for the Packers.

James Starks was benched in this contest. Starks started, but managed just 1 yard on 4 attempts before being taken out of the game.    The Texans were already horrible offensively, so it didn't help that they sustained an injury to a major player in the early going.
